Cafe Volare is a special place to eat.
In Las Vegas, "special" usually means cheap buffets or 24-hour steak & eggs but at Volare, "special" means unique, outstanding and authentic.
Cafe Volare is owned and operated by a longtime Las Vegas family who are originally from Italy.
These good people made a name here in the marble business and Italians know their marble.
(Just ask Michelangelo's friend David.
)  Italianos also view food as art and here at Cafe Volare, they take their time preparing fresh pasta, delicious eggs, crispy salads and crunchy sandwiches and it is well worth the brief wait!
On Valley View just south of Trop with easy parking, the brisk breakfast and business lunch crowd can come and go, plus Volare offers high speed internet, but there's no need to rush.
Rome wasn't built in a day.
Fly to Las Vegas and then head to Volare, "away from the maddening crowds.

I ordered take-out from this place during my lunch break.
I got my order a few minutes after ordering...and when I got back to my office, I had someone else's order!
Of course, I called to let the staff at the restaurant know I was given the wrong food and was on my way back.
Once I got there, all I got was "sorry" from the guys that worked there.
Needless to say, the food was actually pretty good.
I had a Caprese panini which was amazing and it was such a big portion that I only ate half of it.
I also had the Rosemary roasted potatoes which tasted good, but were drenched in oil.
I'll probably go back to this place eventually, but might dine-in next time and maybe I'll skip the potatoes.

