I was tired of the same old lunch options.
I searched for a new idea and Yelp led me to Cafe Volare.
It's bright Italian cafe in a industrial business park that specializes in breakfast and lunch.
My first visit I had the Classic Panini ($8.95) with roasted potatoes.
I preferred classic with ham, arugula and cheese to the Caprese ($7.95).
Subtle difference, but I like the addition of ham next time I'll upgrade to prosciutto.
These paninis remind me of those I had in Italy.
They are simple, fresh and tasty.
The roasted potatoes are rich with rosemary flavor and satisfying.
I'm yet to try breakfast or pasta.
Maybe next time?

